In a skillet, saute onion in butter until tender. Stir in milk, mustard, salt and pepper; bring to a boil. Remove from the heat; stir in potatoes and mix well. Stir in egg yolks until smooth. Cool at room temperature for 15 minutes. Stir in the cheese if desired. In a small mixing bowl, beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Fold into potato mixture. spoon into a greased 1-qt. baking dish. bake at 350 degrees F for 40-45 minutes or until puffed and lightly browned.